-- TJX sees revenue in line with estimates
-- 
-- Tue Aug 14, 2007 11:45am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/14/us-tjx-outlook-idUSN1443500720070814

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Off-price retailer TJX Cos. Inc. ( TJX.N ) said on Tuesday it expects third-quarter revenue of $4.8 billion, in line with analysts' estimates, according to Reuters Estimates. 

 TJX also said it expects same-store sales to rise 3 percent to 4 percent for August. (See  here  for "Shop Talk" -- Reuters' retail and consumer blog)